                            <section id="what-are-cookies" class="legal-section">
                                <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
                                <p>
                                    Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device
                                    (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit our website.
                                    They help us recognize your device and remember certain
                                    information about your preferences or past actions.
                                </p>

                                <p>
                                    Similar technologies include web beacons, pixels, and local
                                    storage, which we may also use to enhance your experience on
                                    our platform.
                                </p>

                                <div class="legal-info-box">
                                    <h4>🍪 Quick Fact</h4>
                                    <p>
                                        Cookies cannot harm your device or access your personal
                                        files. They simply store small pieces of information to
                                        make your browsing experience better.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </section>

                            <section id="why-we-use" class="legal-section">
                                <h2>2. Why We Use Cookies</h2>
                                <p>
                                    We use cookies and similar technologies to provide you with
                                    the best possible learning experience. Specifically, we use
                                    them to:
                                </p>

                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Keep you logged in:</strong> Remember your login
                                        session so you don't have to sign in repeatedly
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Save your progress:</strong> Track your course
                                        progress and resume where you left off
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Personalize content:</strong> Show you relevant
                                        courses and recommendations based on your interests
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Improve performance:</strong> Load pages faster
                                        and provide a smoother user experience
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Analyze usage:</strong> Understand how our
                                        platform is used to make improvements
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Ensure security:</strong> Protect against
                                        fraudulent activity and maintain platform security
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </section>

                            <section id="types-of-cookies" class="legal-section">
                                <h2>3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
                                <p>
                                    We categorize cookies based on their purpose and duration:
                                </p>

                                <div class="legal-contact-grid">
                                    <div class="legal-contact-card">
                                        <h4>Session Cookies</h4>
                                        <p>
                                            Temporary cookies that are deleted when you close your
                                            browser. These are essential for basic functionality.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="legal-contact-card">
                                        <h4>Persistent Cookies</h4>
                                        <p>
                                            Remain on your device for a specified period or until
                                            you delete them. These remember your preferences across
                                            visits.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="legal-contact-card">
                                        <h4>First-Party Cookies</h4>
                                        <p>
                                            Set directly by Nihongo Sekai to provide core
                                            functionality and improve your experience.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="legal-contact-card">
                                        <h4>Third-Party Cookies</h4>
                                        <p>
                                            Set by external services we use, such as analytics
                                            providers or video hosting platforms.
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>

                            <section id="essential-cookies" class="legal-section">
                                <h2>4. Essential Cookies</h2>
                                <p>
                                    These cookies are necessary for our website to function
                                    properly. You cannot opt out of these cookies if you want to
                                    use our Service.
                                </p>

